  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Progranulin blood concentrations in patients with sepsis will be analysed in relation to
      disease status in order to validate progranulin as a biomarker for sepsis. Patients
      undergoing cardiac surgery will serve as controls.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Single nucleotide polymorphisms with known effects on Progranulin plasma concentrations will
      be assessed in a separate analysis. Expression levels of microRNAs isolated from plasma,
      circulating exosomes and blood cells will be determined by next-generation sequencing to
      characterize epigenetic influences on progranulin plasma levels.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
